Of course! A Kernel is the heart of any operating system, so the README.md should sound technical, robust, and reliable. Here is a proposal balanced between modern and compatible: Carl Kernel 🧠 The high-performance core for hardware of all eras. This repository contains the Carl OS Kernel, an optimized fork designed to offer ultra-efficient process management. Its architecture is designed to squeeze every clock cycle in next-generation CPUs without abandoning instruction support for older processors. Technical Features Dynamic Task Scheduler: Optimized to reduce latency in desktop applications. Adaptive Memory Management: Paging algorithms that allow Carl OS to run on machines with low RAM without compromising stability. Retro-Compatibility Drivers: Extended support for legacy video and network drivers.
